你真该在场。

186
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,680
Everyone was staring and laughing.
所有人都在盯着看，哈哈大笑。

187
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,680
It was hilarious.
太搞笑了。

188
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:31,280
Okay, so there was a lot of different uses of past tense here in this dialogue, wasn't
好，所以这个对话里有很多不同的过去时态用法，对吧？

189
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:32,280
there?
对吧？

190
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:36,000
When he was telling a story that happened, he used the past a lot.
当他讲一个发生过的故事时，他用了很多过去时。

191
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:44,280
Well, let's now, as promised, look at past simple and past progressive in Grammar Breakdown.
好，我们现在按承诺，在语法解析中看看一般过去时和过去进行时。

192
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,680
Grammar Breakdown.
语法解析。

193
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:52,360
Okay, Marco, before we start our discussion, why don't we hear one example of past simple
好，Marco，在我们开始讨论之前，我们先听一个一般过去时的例子

194
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:57,600
and one example of past progressive?
和一个过去进行时的例子。

195
00:07:57,600 --> 00:08:02,280
You know, just last week, I ran into Matt as well.
你知道吗，就在上周，我也偶然遇见了Matt。

196
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:06,920
Well, we were talking and catching up on what we've been doing.
嗯，我们正在聊天，聊聊最近在做什么。

197
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:13,240
Okay, so we heard that just last week, I ran into Matt.
好，所以我们听到“就在上周，我偶然遇见了Matt”。

198
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,640
So we discussed what run into means.
我们讨论过run into的意思。

199
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:17,720
Yep, to meet someone by surprise.
是的，意外遇见某人。

200
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,720
All right.
好的。

201
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:21,120
And now this structure is the simple past, right?
那么这个结构就是一般过去时，对吧？

202
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,120
Yep.
是的。

203
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:26,320
Now the second example that we heard was, we were talking and catching up.
现在我们听到的第二个例子是，我们当时正在聊天叙旧。

204
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:29,840
Okay, so let's look at the difference in meaning here.
好的，那我们来看看这里意思上的区别。

205
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:33,240
I ran into Matt, happened in the past, right?
我偶遇了马特，这件事发生在过去，对吧？

206
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,320
Right, simple past.
对，一般过去时。

207
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:36,680
But one moment in the past.
但只是过去的一个时间点。

208
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:39,480
So the action finished, concluded.
所以这个动作完成了，结束了。

209
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:42,080
Started and finished all around the same time.
开始和结束几乎在同一时间。

210
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,560
So it's one simple moment.
所以它是一个简单的时间点。

211
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:45,560
Okay.
好的。

212
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:49,960
Now, the other example is in the past progressive.
现在，另一个例子是过去进行时。

213
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:54,600
So the action was happening for a longer period of time.
所以这个动作持续了更长的时间。

214
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,600
Yeah.
是的。

215
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:59,800
So let's attach some times to this.
那我们给这个加上一些时间点。

216
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:03,360
Maybe you ran into Matt at 8.04.
也许你在8点04分偶遇了马特。

217
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,120
Okay.
好的。

218
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:08,620
And so the action started at 8.04.
所以这个动作从8点04分开始。

219
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:13,320
But you were talking and catching up from 8.05 until 9.05.
但你们从8点05分一直聊天叙旧到9点05分。

220
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,400
Okay.
好的。

221
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,000
So you were talking for an hour.
所以你们聊了一个小时。

222
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,000
Right.
对。

223
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:22,720
So it's the past progressive you use when the action is happening for a longer period
所以当动作持续较长时间时，你就用过去进行时。

224
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,720
of time.


225
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:29,560
So to better understand this, let's have another example.
为了更好地理解这一点，我们再举一个例子。

226
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:34,160
Matt saw a mouse run under his chair and he completely lost it.
马特看到一只老鼠跑到他椅子下面，他完全失控了。

227
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:36,600
Everyone was staring and laughing.
大家都在盯着看并大笑。

228
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:41,400
So as we heard in the example, he saw a mouse run under his chair.
就像我们在例子中听到的，他看到一只老鼠跑到他椅子下面。

229
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:44,040
So a quick action that started and finished quickly.
所以这是一个快速开始并快速结束的动作。

230
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,040
Okay.
好的。

231
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:46,840
He saw the mouse and it ran under the chair.
他看到了老鼠，老鼠跑到了椅子下面。

232
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,840
Yeah.
是的。

233
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:53,420
Now, the second example we heard was, everyone was staring and laughing.
现在，我们听到的第二个例子是，大家都在盯着看并大笑。

234
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:55,920
So maybe this happened over four or five minutes.
所以这可能持续了四五分钟。

235
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:56,920
Okay.
好的。

236
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:01,120
So people were looking at him and laughing and talking about how he was screaming like
所以人们看着他，笑着，谈论他像女孩一样尖叫的样子。

237
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,120
a girl.


238
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,120
Yes.
是的。

239
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,120
Okay.
好的。

240
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:07,800
So that's the main difference between the simple past and the past progressive.
这就是一般过去时和过去进行时的主要区别。

241
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:10,280
The amount of time that the action happened.
动作发生的时间长度。

242
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,280
Yep.
是的。

243
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,280
All right.
好的。

244
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:14,800
Well, now that we understand a little bit more about the past tense, why don't we hear
好了，既然我们对过去时态有了更多了解，不如我们第三次听对话，在上下文中再听一遍。

245
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:25,200
it again in context by listening to the dialogue for a third time.


246
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:29,420
Mike, what's going on, man?
迈克，怎么了，老兄？

247
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,420
Long time no see.
好久不见。

248
00:10:30,420 --> 00:10:31,420
Hey, Pat.
嘿，帕特。

249
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:32,420
Yeah.
是啊。

250
00:10:32,420 --> 00:10:33,420
I haven't seen you in ages.
我好久没见到你了。

251
00:10:33,420 --> 00:10:34,420
How's it going?
你怎么样？

252
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:35,420
Things are going great.
一切都很好。

253
00:10:35,420 --> 00:10:36,800
It's funny running into you like this.
这样偶遇你真有意思。

254
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:37,800
Small world, huh?
世界真小，是吧？

255
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:40,240
You know, just last week I ran into Matt as well.
你知道吗，就在上周我也偶遇了马特。

256
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,240
Yeah.
是啊。

257
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,240
How's he doing?
他怎么样？

258
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,240
He's doing well.
他挺好的。

259
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,800
We went out for a couple of beers and the funniest thing happened.
我们出去喝了几杯啤酒，然后发生了最有趣的事。

260
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:46,800
Oh yeah?
哦，是吗？

261
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:51,120
Well, we were talking and catching up on what we've been doing, talking about work and family
嗯，我们当时正在聊天叙旧，聊着工作和家庭，

262
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:54,800
when all of a sudden Matt saw a mouse run under the chair and he completely lost it.
突然马特看到一只老鼠跑到椅子下面，他完全失控了。

263
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,600
He started freaking out and screaming.
他开始惊慌失措，尖叫起来。

264
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,600
Really?
真的吗？

265
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,600
Yeah.
是啊。

266
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:01,280
And the funniest thing was, then he jumped onto his chair and started shrieking like
最有趣的是，然后他跳上椅子，像女孩一样尖叫起来。

267
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,280
a girl.


268
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:03,280
He should have been there.
你真该在场。

269
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:04,700
Everyone was staring and laughing.
大家都在盯着看并大笑。

270
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:05,700
It was hilarious.
太搞笑了。

271
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:06,700
Okay.
好的。

272
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:07,700
Perfect.
完美。

273
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:14,560
So now that we understand the words and the grammar behind it, there are some interesting
好了，现在我们理解了单词和背后的语法，这里还有一些有趣的短语，你可以和朋友随意使用。

274
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:17,720
phrases here that you can use casually with your friends.


275
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:18,720
Yeah.
是的。

276
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:24,360
There's actually a lot of great sort of meeting and greeting and saying hello language.
实际上有很多很好的见面问候用语。

277
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:30,360
So for example, when they met up, since they were old friends, he said, Hey, Pat.
比如，当他们见面时，因为是老朋友，他说，嘿，帕特。

278
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,360
Hey.
嘿。

279
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,360
Okay.
好的。

280
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,360
So this word, hey.
所以这个词，嘿。

281
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,360
It's kind of like hi.
有点像嗨。

282
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,360
It's hi, right?
就是嗨，对吧？

283
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,360
Yep.
是的。

284
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,040
So you can use it to get somebody's attention, right?
所以你可以用它来引起别人的注意，对吧？

285
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,040
Like, Hey, I'm over here.
比如，嘿，我在这儿。

286
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:40,040
Hey, waiter.
嘿，服务员。

287
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:41,040
Okay.
好的。

288
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,040
Yeah.
是的。

289
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,040
But in this case, like, Hey, how's it going?
但在这个情况下，就像，嘿，你怎么样？

290
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,040
Or hi.
或者嗨。

291
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:45,040
Yeah.
是的。

292
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,720
So it's a really friendly and informal way of saying hi.
所以这是一种非常友好和非正式的说嗨的方式。

293
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,720
Okay.
好的。

294
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:50,440
And then he asked, how's it going?
然后他问，你怎么样？

295
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,760
How's it going?
你怎么样？

296
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:54,400
So again, this is a way of saying, how are you?
同样，这是一种说“你好吗？”的方式。

297
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,400
Yeah.
是的。

298
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,520
Marco, what's the correct answer to this greeting?
马可，对这个问候的正确回答是什么？

299
00:11:57,520 --> 00:12:01,080
Well, well, for example, he said, things are going great.
嗯，比如，他说，一切都很好。

300
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,080
Right.
对。

301
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,240
You can say, yeah, things are great.
你可以说，是啊，一切都很好。

302
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,840
Or I'm doing well.
或者我挺好的。

303
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:05,840
Yeah.
是的。

304
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,840
Or even great.
甚至可以说很好。

305
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:07,840
Great.
很好。

306
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:08,840
Yeah.
是的。

307
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,840
So how's it going?
所以“你怎么样？”

308
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,840
Oh, it's great.
哦，很好。

309
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:11,840
Yeah.
是的。

310
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:12,840
Right.
对。

311
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:16,880
Now, another one that we didn't see in the dialogue, but it's very popular is when somebody
现在，另一个我们在对话中没有看到，但很常见的问候是，当有人问，嘿，怎么了？

312
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,880
asks, Hey, what's up?


313
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:19,880
Yeah.
是的。

314
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:20,880
What's up?
怎么了？

315
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:23,480
So again, what is the right way to answer this question?
同样，回答这个问题的正确方式是什么？

316
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:24,480
All right.
好的。

317
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,360
So when somebody says, what's up?
所以当有人说，怎么了？

318
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:28,240
You can say, well, not much.
你可以说，嗯，没什么。

319
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:31,920
Or if maybe you have news or something that you want to share, you would say, well, I
或者如果你有消息或想分享的事情，你会说，嗯，我刚从医生办公室回来。

320
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:34,560
just got back from the doctor's office.


321
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:35,560
Yeah.
是的。

322
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,360
But you wouldn't say, fine, thank you.
但你不能说，很好，谢谢。

323
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,720
Or you wouldn't say, very good.
或者你不能说，非常好。

324
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:42,600
Or any of these other common answers to what's up.
或者其他这些常见的回答。

325
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,600
That's right.
没错。

326
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,600
It can be a little bit tricky.
这可能有点棘手。

327
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,600
Yeah.
是的。

328
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:49,240
So the rule is, the normal thing to say when someone says, hey, what's up?
所以规则是，当有人说，嘿，怎么了？通常的回答是。

329
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,600
Is nothing much.
没什么。

330
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,600
Not much.
没什么。

331
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,600
Yep.
是的。

332
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,600
All right.
好的。

333
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:54,720
So interesting ways of greeting casually with people, right?
所以这些是和朋友随意问候的有趣方式，对吧？

334
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:57,960
You wouldn't use this fully with your boss, maybe, or in an office setting.
你可能不会对老板或在办公室场合完全这样用。

335
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:58,960
Yeah.
是的。

336
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,360
More useful with your friends.
对朋友更有用。

337
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:01,360
Okay.
好的。

338
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:05,600
So if you have any other questions or have any other informal greetings that you would
所以如果你有其他问题，或者有其他非正式问候语想和我们分享，请来EnglishPod.com。

339
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:08,400
like to share with us, come to EnglishPod.com.


340
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:09,400
Yeah.
是的。

341
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:14,040
Marco and I are always around to answer your questions and we look forward to hearing from
马可和我随时都在回答你的问题，我们期待收到你的消息。

342
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,040
you.


343
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:16,040
So until next time.
所以下次再见。

344
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,040
Bye.
再见。

345
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:32,800
Have a great day.
祝你有美好的一天。
